com.apriori.choice

Interface Choice.VisitorOfFour<A,B,C,D,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the type of the choice's first option
    B - the type of the choice's second option
    C - the type of the choice's third option
    D - the type of the choice's fourth option
    R - the result type from visiting the choice
    All Superinterfaces:
    Choice.VisitorOfThree<A,B,C,R>, Choice.VisitorOfTwo<A,B,R>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Choice.VisitorOfFive<A,B,C,D,E,R>
    Enclosing interface:
    Choice<A,B>

    public static interface Choice.VisitorOfFour<A,B,C,D,R>
extends Choice.VisitorOfThree<A,B,C,R>
    A visitor for a choice with four options. When passed to OfFour#visit(Choices.VisitorOfFour), one of the visit* methods will be invoked, depending on which option is present.
